<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 23 at 6:28PM EDT until March 23 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 645 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN RICHLAND AND SOUTHERN ASHLAND COUNTIES...
At 628 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hayesville, or
9 miles south of Ashland, moving northeast at 70 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to vehicles is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Butler, Perrysville and Mifflin.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for north central
Ohio.
For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
